{
  "stem": "5103.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And only if the old gentleman-- Father Visser, we called him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She was Mother Visser and he was Father Visser.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "If he said it was OK and if the coast was clear.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because they used to get visitors and things.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Life went on downstairs absolutely, as though nothing was happening in the house upstairs.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there was all that-- there were now three generations.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was my grandfather, my uncle who was 10 years younger than my father, then my mother and my father, and then me.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now when you come into a situation like that in a room where you live in from the morning to the night, you get onto each other's nerves regardless of how good you are.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "An old man, he wants to do something, you're sitting with your chair this way, he doesn't want to move.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I want to go there, he doesn't want me to go.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then if food came up-- we used to eat upstairs in that room-- if food came up, there was arguments about she's got more than he.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He's got more than you.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Why are you eating this?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Why are you giving your child more than us?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You've [? got ?] more than this.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Like-- this went on because there was nothing else to do, only to look at one another and to see that-- and yet, we loved each other and we wanted to make it, but it was like a-- a terrible tension.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother taught me how to knit, my mother taught me how to sew.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother taught me how to draw-- like drawing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Like, she'd get some thing-- little painting of some magazine or something that the people had downstairs, and I would copy it and I drew.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
